  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ gas 4</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Strip your <strong>sage leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597675467981-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597675467981-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597675467981-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597675467981-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1597675467981-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> and weigh out 60g <span class=\"text-purple\">[90g]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[120g]</span> (roughly 1/4!)</p><p>Dice the 60g <span class=\"text-purple\">[90g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[120g]</span> of <strong>sweet potato</strong> and set the remaining aside (you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced shallot</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>chopped sage </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597675472038-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597675472038-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597675472038-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597675472038-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597675472038-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>diced sweet potato</strong> and cook for a further 1-2 min</p><p>Meanwhile, dice your<strong> mushrooms</strong> roughly</p><p>Add the <strong>diced mushrooms</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a splash of <strong>water</strong> to the pan, then cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1597675476290-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1597675476290-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1597675476290-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1597675476290-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1597675476290-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> into the pan with 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 4-5 min or until the stock has been absorbed and the sweet potato is tender</p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining sweet potato</strong> and <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into thin disc shapes (as finely as you can) – these are your <strong>potato crisps</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>kale</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1597675480405-x200.jpg",
