    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin </strong>and cut into 2 <span class=\"text-purple\">[3]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4]</span></p><p>Line a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>tin foil</strong> and add the <strong>pastry</strong></p><p>Divide the<strong> pasty filling</strong> into 2 <span class=\"text-purple\">[3]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4] </span>and add the mixture to one corner of each</p><p>Fold the corner over to make a triangle shape and crimp the edges with a fork to seal each pasty</p>",
